imperative for us to leave Taos for New York (a grave sickness in the family). I shall telephone you at the New Yorker next week on the chance you may be there. There is a number of things that I would like to discuss with you.

Best love to you and Andy.





TO: PROF. REUBEN BROWER1

CC, 1 p.

Ithaca, N. Y.





September 10, 1954

Dear Mr. Brower,

